OK, I'm a bit confused here.  quay.io/containers/skopeo is supposed to be a repo containing tags like :latest, :v1.9.0, etc.  

So a pull of docker://quay.io/skopeo/stable:latest and then a pull of docker://quay.io/containers/skopeo:latest is supposed to return different images containing the same makeup.  

@cevich the quay.io/containers/{project} repos all look to have been turned into pointers to the quay.io/{project}/stable repos.  Was that intentional or was that an artifact of the fun security drill we had with the images a month or so ago?
